        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:42PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Emporia, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Strong wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail damage to outdoor objects and
vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Emporia.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 between mile markers 128 and 135.
Kansas Turnpike between mile markers 118 and 134.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
